<br>
“So, what? Is this the place?”<br>
<br>
“That’s what the ghouls said.”<br>
<br>
Crowley and Vicious stood in the upscale late-dining restaurant on the outskirts of San Diego. This was where the damned Sabbat ghouls Crowley had interrogated in Santa Carla had lead them.  <br>
<br>
Crowley summoned his new-found powers of Auspex. It was like seeing the world through new eyes. Every detail of the room suddenly became clear. The emotions of the occupants became tangible. Their life forces….<br>
<br>
Crowley’s attention turned to a young woman. She was beautiful, of what seemed to be of mixed Anglo-Latino heritage. She didn’t look like she could’ve been older than 20, though based on what his senses were telling him, appearances really didn’t mean much.  <br>
<br>
“Vicious, that woman. Check her out.”<br>
<br>
Vicious turned his head and looked at the woman. “Yeah, she’s fine, Crowley. No question about that. But, uh… that’s not why we’re here.”<br>
<br>
Despite himself, Crowley could not keep the irritation out of his hushed voice. “I meant her aura.” <br>
<br>
“Oh.” Vicious replied. “Right. I knew that.”<br>
<br>
“Perhaps its time we introduced ourselves to one of the locals.” <br>
<br>
Crowley and Vicious struck up a conversation with the young woman. Within a few minutes, and with some well-chosen words and the discreet use of a few disciplines, they had confirmed that the woman’s name was Juana, and that she was the childe of the quarry, Joseph Stein. Her Sire, who had many havens, was away right now on Sabbat business. Juana made her own haven in the apartment above the restaurant, and handled the night to night running of the place.    <br>
 <br>
Crowley found a chance to pull Vicious aside for a moment and lowered his voice.<br>
<br>
 “Vicious, this is the perfect opportunity. I don’t think she’s bound to him. Tell you what, you go check out those other leads, and I’ll see what I can find out about Stein’s operation from her. By the time you get back, I should have him safely under wraps. Then we can do what we want to him.”<br>
<br>
Vicious grinned. “Good idea, Crowley! You bag the babe, I'll go find something flammable!&quot; He ran off into the night before Crowley could respond.<br>
<br>
Crowley stood agape for a full second before recovering. He didn’t know whether to be pissed at Vicious for saying something like that within earshot of Juana… or amused. He finally decided on the latter. Being away from Santa Carla changed things; suddenly the emphasis was no longer the petty squabbles and deal-making of Elysium but on their mission. The Sabbat. The enemy. If left to their own devices, those monsters would rise up and consume the world. They would bring about the very Gehenna they claimed to combat. Crowley knew he had to do everything he could to prevent that. <br>
 <br>
Crowley turned back to Juana and smiled. He looked deeply into her beautiful eyes. <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>“Please forget what my friend just said.”</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> He commanded. The look of surprise that had been on her face vanished and was once again replaced by a delightful smile. Crowley’s voice now dripped honey as he gazed longingly into her eyes. “Now please, tell me more about yourself. How exactly did you meet Mr. Stein?”<br>
<br>
