<br>
Vicious spun around and jogged off. It had been a long, mostly boring drive, but here he was. San Diego. Sabbat land. Of course, there were advantages to being here. One of them being the ability to actually kill other vampires. He hadn’t done that in… well…. ever. Sure, he had seen them killed, but he was never the lucky one who struck the final blow. Bah.<br>
<br>
But now came the fun part. Finding something flammable! No, wait. Vicious was on a mission.  Nothing fancy like “You must save the world from Gehenna! Oh no!” or “You must save the Prince from the Sabbat! Oh no!”, but more like “You must save us ALL from the Sabbat! Oh yes!” This promised to be fun and entertaining, if not a bit on the stressful side. Regardless, one could always find Sabbat if one knew where to look, and if there was one group of antitribu that Vicious knew well, it was the Toreador. He loved those crazy motherfuckers.<br>
<br>
Sheer luck. Vicious had found himself a lovely BDSM club fifteen minutes down the street from the restaurant. Talk about convenient! Vicious looked down. Dressed in a messy suit with the button-up untucked, he looked more like he’d been hit by a car recently. That wasn’t really the type of environment one wore this kind of clothes in. But where could he find clothing to match the locale?<br>
<br>
Screw it. No one would care what he was wearing so long as he was willing to punch someone. Or whip them.Or cane them. Or who knows what else. Vicious paid the cover charge and headed inside. About ten seconds later he regretted it, as some random woman descended on him and started trying to claw him out of his clothing right in the middle of what looked like some kind of lobby. There was a lot of black leather, and a lot of flashing lights, and this amounted to what could’ve been a huge headache if Vicious hadn’t toned down his enhanced sight. And the music. Sweet father in hell! The horrible, horrible music! It sounded like a cat trying to go to the bathroom through a sewn up anus…. Not that Vicious knew what that sounded like. A moment of staring at this woman revealed her to be mortal. Vicious firmly removed her. She started to approach again when stopped her with a glare and slowly drew back his sleeve, revealing his knife sheaths. Her eyes got wide for a moment, and she quickly ran off. Vicious knew she’d be summoning a bouncer or some guy in a gimp suit to remove him from the club…. Or maybe violate him in ways that he thought weren’t possible for a human, but he didn’t need that much time. He just needed to (hopefully) find a vampire and get out. Vicious wandered around the main areas, staring intently at people. Some stared back. Others left in digust. One grabbed him by the crotch and started shaking. That was disturbing and painful. However, in five minutes of searching, he’d found nothing, and a very large and scary-looking fellow was approaching him at speeds rivalling that of a person walking really fast. Vicious smiled at the man as he approached, rounded a corner that led into a hallway which hopefully led either out or into some kind of private room area where he could hide, and burst into Celerity, clearing the hallway and ducking into an empty room.<br>
<br>
Or so he thought!<br>
<br>
Wait…. Nope. It was empty. <br>
<br>
Vicious ducked behind a chair…. A chair with straps… ick…. And waited. Footsteps walked by, but did not enter. Vicious waited. Then he got bored and left the room, eager to engage in a proper battle to the death with any number of massive bouncers. Stepping into the hallway, he ran straight into a woman wearing knee-high boots and a leather one-piece. Vicious stared at her for a second before his mind caught up with his defunct sex-drive. Libido later!<br>
<br>
“Welcome to The Whip. Can I help you in any way?” the woman asked. Vicious cocked his head to the side. That was unexpected.<br>
<br>
“Uhhh… yeah. I’m looking for the room with the knives and the cutting and the bleeding.” He replied. The two of them stared at one another for about twenty seconds before the woman smiled.<br>
<br>
“Yes, of course. Right this way, sir.” She said, turning and walking off. Vicious blinked before starting off after her. What were the chances? A few moments later, Vicious stood in front of a door, with another bouncer-type standing guard. The woman looked at Vicious and once again smiled.<br>
<br>
“For reasons of safety, Richard will have to…. Frisk you.” She said. Vicious smiled and looked directly into her eyes.<br>
<br>
“No he doesn’t.” He said cooly. The woman blinked, and then smiled again.<br>
<br>
“Yes he does.”<br>
<br>
Damnit! He hadn’t spontaneously developed Dominate! That threw his entire plan of attack into turmoil! Vicious faced Richard and waited as he removed Vicious’ staff  and knives from his clothing. This could not be allowed. Vicious nodded at the hostess, who smiled, turned, and went off to do something more interesting. Vicious turned and pointed at his staff.<br>
<br>
“Whatever you do, don’t hold this end to your head and push the button.” He said. Richard glared at him.<br>
<br>
“Nice try.” Vicious smiled, “It was, wasn’t it?”. Then he slammed his hand out and pushed the button. The staff extended and hit Richard in the foot, causing him to drop it. Vicious caught it in mid-air and swung around, catching Richard on the temple and slamming him against the wall. Richard slumped into Vicious’ already waiting arms, where he was dragged into a room containing a bed…. With straps…. And left on the ground. Vicious returned to the room and entered, fully armed and ready to go.<br>
<br>
The room was spacious, containing all kinds of great furniture. Some of it didn’t even have straps. A lone woman with pale white skin and red hair in a red silk gown lay sprawled across a couch, staring thoughtfully at the door, which now contained Vicious. He stared back, and after a moment, her pale aura melted into view. Finally. One of those freaky Sabbat dominatrixes. Fun! The woman didn’t seem as happy to see him, though.<br>
<br>
“Did you kill him, or just beat him up a bit?” she asked. Vicious shrugged.<br>
<br>
“He was in the way.” He said. She sat up and stretched.<br>
<br>
“So, are you here to try to kill me or something?” she asked. Vicious once again shrugged. He wasn’t in the mood for interrogation right now, and really just wanted to get some info as quickly as possible.<br>
<br>
“Not unless you give me a reason to. I’m looking for other vampires. Care to fill me in?” Vicious hoped that his straight-to-the-point manner would make this go faster. He really wanted to go back and see how Crowley was doing. If worst came to worst, he didn’t know if Crowley could hold his own in a fight, and damnit, Vicious kinda liked the guy! The woman had already stood up and was approaching him, staring at him intently.<br>
<br>
“Is that all you’re looking for?” The woman said. Vicious glared. That did it.<br>
<br>
“Look, I’m in a hurry and I don’t have time for games. Can you help me out or not?” Vicious snarled. This was taking too long, and so far it had only taken about a minute.<br>
<br>
“So you’re not in the mood to….pla…. hey!” the woman stopped as Vicious just turned around and started to walk out. “I haven’t got the time or inclination for this. I’ll get my info elsewhere.”<br>
<br>
“Look, if you’re interested in joining us, you can’t just walk in here and…ccchhhhh” Vicious had blurred back and now had his hand around her throat, slowly lifting her up and glaring into her eyes.<br>
<br>
“I can do whatever the fuck I want. Now are you going to tell me what I want to know, or am I going to set you on fire? I hear you Sabbat have much more lax rules regarding destruction than that stupid Camarilla does, you annoying bitch.” Fear suddenly became apparent in her expression and Vicious dropped her, drawing a knife from its sheath and stabbing suddenly, barely pricking the end of her nose. She lost it.<br>
<br>
“Alright, alright! If you go downtown, there’s a theater called “Five Star”. Right next to it is a big apartment complex. You can’t miss it. Go to apartment #32 and tell them that Kendra sent you. They’ll give you the information you need. Now please go away!”<br>
<br>
Vicious smiled. Sure, it might be a trap, but Vicious was just as good at avoiding them as he was at setting them. He turned and left. That was one errand out of the way….<br>
<br>
As he left, the woman spoke one last time…<br>
<br>
“You’re pretty accurate with that knife of yours.”<br>
<br>
“I was aiming for your eye.”<br>
