<br>
“You know what your sire has planned for you, don’t you?”<br>
<br>
Crowley and Juana lay sprawled naked in bed in Juana’s apartment above the restaurant, their clothes strewn all over the floor. They had shared each other’s blood, and neither had any immediate desire to leave the other. <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Mission be damned.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> Crowley thought. <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>I’ll take Stein’s childe, and have his head.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
“When the time is right, he’s going to present you to one of the local packs. He will make a gift out of you.” Crowley’s voice dripped concern as he caressed the woman wrapped in his arms. “They will take you into their Vaulderie. You’ll be like a slave to them.”  He gently tipped her chin until she faced him. “They will use you to kill and destroy and pillage. They will use you to rape and subvert. When they are finished, there will be nothing left of you but the Beast that rages within.”<br>
<br>
Crowley looked at her with as much compassion as he could summon. “Is that what you want?”<br>
<br>
She gazed back at him. “Can you stop it from happening?”<br>
<br>
He smiled slyly. “If you let me try.”<br>
<br>
Suddenly Crowley heard a crashing noise from inside the apartment. Before he could react, a man appeared in the doorway of the bedroom. He was dressed entirely in black with a long black jacket that came down to his knees. That wasn’t what Crowley noticed the most about him, however. That would be the long, shadowy tentacles emanating from his being. Also catching Crowley’s eye was that the man appeared very, very angry. <br>
<br>
Crowley maintained his composure and focused his will. “Ah, Mr. Stein. I’ve been expecting you. Won’t you please have a seat, and don’t move or attack anyone.”<br>
<br>
If Stein hadn’t been angry before, he was angry now. <br>
<br>
With a roar, tentacles wrapped around Crowley, ripping him out of the bed. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Crap. Crowley thought. <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>I’ve met someone with thicker blood than m</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <br>
 <br>
By the time he finished that thought, Crowley body had been smashed against the wall. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Got to get my feet under me… my only chance…</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Unfortunately, Stein had other ideas. <br>
<br>
An instant later, Crowley had been smashed THROUGH the wall. Fortitude aside, Stein was starting to do some damage. Some subconscious region of Crowley’s brain told him he was now in the kitchen of Juana’s apartment. Another subconscious region told him he had just heard Juana yelling something at her Sire, only to be knocked out of the way. A very conscious region of Crowley’s mind felt the black tentacles, and then actual hands, wrapping around his neck. <br>
<br>
Crowley knew that he couldn’t be strangled. He didn’t even have to breathe. Somehow, that wasn’t making him feel better at the moment, and Crowley could feel himself losing consciousness as he was being driven into torpor and most assuredly Final Death…<br>
<br>
Suddenly Crowley heard a loud THUMP! He glanced up to see Vicious, staff in hand, standing over a woozy Joseph Stein.<br>
<br>
“Hey, Crowley.” Vicious grinned. “Need any help?”<br>
