<br>
Vicious turned and ran outside, up the steps to the apartment above the restaurant, and slammed his foot into the door, cracking the center and causing the door to break off the top hinge. Tearing a large piece of the door off, Vicious ran in the direction of what sounded like some woman screaming something, and another crash. A much bigger crash. Hey, maybe Crowley had just sent that fucker through a… nope.<br>
<br>
What looked like a hentai tentacle rape nightmare was slowly advancing on what looked like a naked Crowley, and there was a naked screaming spanish chick in the bed. Vicious glared at the woman. It was that Juana bitch. She’d set Crowley up. He lunged at her, smashing her face with his left hand while slamming his stake into her chest with the other. The punch itself was enough to knock her off the bed onto the floor, where she lay completely motionless, the stake having done its job. Vicious turned to see the Lasombra trying to choke Crowley to death. What a moron. Vicious jumped into the air, launching himself at the back of the Lasombra, and clubbed him with the handle of his staff. The vampire fell backwards and off of Crowley. Vicious extended the staff and placed it behind his neck, using it to support his arms in a relaxed position. <br>
<br>
“Hey Crowley. Need any help?” Vicious asked as the Lasombra stood up and snarled something in Spanish. Vicious doesn’t speak Spanish, so that won’t be covered here. Deal.<br>
<br>
Vicious heard something cutting the air behind him and spun his staff around, deflecting one tentacle into another before gracefully turning back to face the Lasombra.<br>
<br>
“Look, pal. Despite the fact that you’d like to kill Señor Crowley, that would mean the death of the only Ventrue so far who I don’t want to kill horribly with a butter knife. So if you were to kill him, that would make me angry. You wouldn’t like me when I’m angry!”<br>
<br>
Stein blinked.<br>
<br>
“Shut up, unoriginal little bastard.”<br>
<br>
Vicious glared. “That’s it, asshole. Bring it!”<br>
<br>
Two more tentacles fired out from Vicious left. He dodged back just as he let loose two of his throwing knives, which Stein ducked under as he charged forward, punching at Vicious’ face. Vicious ducked underneath the fist and punched upward, only to miss as Stein fell slightly around Vicious, avoiding the punch and positioning himself behind Vicious. Vicious spun around and swung his staff around, impacting on a shadowy tentacle that had positioned itself between the staff and Stein’s head. Vicious slammed the end of the staff against the wall and let his grip slide up until they had just reached the tentacle, at which point he ran up and along the wall for two steps so that he was facing Stein. Bursting into Celerity, Vicious kicked off the wall at the same time as he slammed his staff into where Stein’s head should have been, but was no longer. Vicious hit the ground, rolled, and lifted his staff in time to block another tentacle that lashed out from in front of him just as everything suddenly went completely black. Vicious heard, at the very last second, something cutting air behind him, and thanks to Celerity was able to duck in time to avoid having his neck stabbed with something sharp. This gave Vicious a direction to attack in, and he did so, missing completely, but clearing himself from the black cloud that hung in the center of the room. Vicious spun around and deflected three more tentacles as they launched themselves toward him, ducking as a fourth splintered the wall behind him. It hovered there for a moment, giving Vicious time to rip a lighter from his jacket pocket, light it, and jam it into the tentacle. It thrashed back and forth before withdrawing, and gave Vicious enough room to dodge Stein’s punch as he appeared out of the shadowy cloud covering most of the room, slamming his fist into the wall and knocking a fist-sized chunk through it. Vicious swung his staff around at Stein’s head, but Stein lifted his other arm and caught it, pulling hard towards himself. Vicious released the staff, allowing Stein to pull it free, and launched himself at Stein, throwing a pair of knives along the way. Stein dodged both knives and ducked as Vicious jumped over him, grabbed his staff and pulled as hard as he could, freeing it from Stein’s distracted grasp, before crashing through the damaged wall and rolling out into the front room, where he spun around and assumed what he assumed was a threatening looking stance. It wasn’t threatening enough.<br>
<br>
Vicious ducked as the four tentacles all stabbed at his head, and barely moved back in time to avoid a fifth tentacle as it suddenly shot out of the ground directly under his face, and then deflected Stein’s kick to the right, rolling clear of Stein as he elbow-dropped onto the position Vicious had been in previously... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bscbnforum58570.showUserPublicProfile?gid=stephencrowley>Stephen Crowley</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://lagoon.freebsd.lublin.pl/~fenix/smieci/graf/rozne/vampire/camarilla.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 240<br> <font color=#FF9300>(6/5/03 4:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fscbnforum58570frm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=108.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://people.ucsc.edu/~mcrupp/camarilla.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Vicious and Crowley's Excellent Adventure - Part Five</span><hr size=1> “Vicious, take cover!” Crowley was on his feet now, and even better, was partially dressed. Even better than those two, he was pissed off, and eager to return the favor he now owed Vicious. <br>
<br>
Vicious apparently understood exactly what Crowley had in mind. With an absurdly athletic flip, Vicious leapt and practically flew over Crowley’s head, landing safely behind him. It was very fortunate Juana had tall ceilings. <br>
<br>
Crowley’s attention was now focused on Stein. As the Lasombra turned to face the Ventrue, Crowley’s eyes started glowing…<br>
<br>
“Tremble in the presence of my faith, monster!”<br>
<br>
Crowley was vaguely aware of Stein’s shadow-powers wilting. He was partially aware of the once-powerful and seemingly invincible Keeper suddenly cowering before him. He was semiconscious of the fact that his eyes were lit up like light-bulbs, and were projecting the raw power of his faith into the world.<br>
<br>
What Crowley was MOST conscious of was going on inside his head.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>This was what you wanted.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> He told himself. <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Camarilla against Sabbat. Ventrue against Lasombra. Order against Chaos. He could feel the power of the ancients flowing through him. He had been chosen for this task. He had been given this gift. Now he was using it to best effect. He was doing the work of the Camarilla; pounding the Sabbat back, making the world a little bit safer. The power and elation he felt were absolutely intoxicating…</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>So why did he feel so incredibly used?</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Crowley was suddenly alerted to Vicious shaking him. <br>
<br>
&quot;Crowley! We won, you can stop trying to Dominate the air molecules now.&quot;<br>
<br>
Crowley looked in the corner and saw Joseph Stein staked body, a look of terror still haunted the Lasombra’s face.<br>
<br>
“Oh. Very good.”<br>
<br>
